node.text:
2/3: ”The starting point of the Soft Side Table was to create something that was both subtle and characterful. Now, these two are often perceived as opposite poles, so the intent was to bring them together through softened surfaces and an understated yet sophisticated functionality,” says Fager, looking across the workshop that acts as part of his studio, located in a barn in the southern Swedish countryside.
—
Explore the story, now via link in bio. #muuto #newperspectives #scandinaviandesign

node.title: The Soft Side Table by Jens Fager

node.text:
Negative Space, a series of artworks created by duo Davide Ronco and Pablo Dorigo for the Ukurant Perspectives 2021 exhibition, supported by Muuto. The pieces can be experienced at both the Ukurant Perspectives 2021 exhibition and the Muuto HQ throughout 3daysofdesign 2021.
—
September 16th — 18th, 2021
Muuto HQ
Østergade 36-38
1100 Copenhagen K

September 16th — 26th, 2021
Ukurant Perspectives 2021, supported by Muuto
Amaliegade 38
1256 Copenhagen K

The Ukurant Perspectives 2021 exhibition, supported by Muuto is officially open! Experience works by 17 incredibly talented designers from across the world, spanning from furniture over ceramics to sculptures and lighting designs, all echoing the idea of creating future new perspectives on design.
—
September 16th — 26th, 2021
Ukurant Perspectives 2021, supported by Muuto
Amaliegade 38
1256 Copenhagen K

Photos by @jonasjacobsvensson

node.text:
The day has finally come for us to invite you into our Muuto HQ in the heart of Copenhagen for 3daysofdesign 2021 once again!

Explore our universe of new perspectives on Scandinavian design alongside our latest design introductions and experience informal meetings with designers Thomas Bentzen and Anderssen & Voll—we can't wait to see you!
—
September 16th — 18th, 2021
Muuto HQ
Østergade 36-38
1100 Copenhagen K

node.text:
The Ukurant Perspectives 2021 exhibition, supported by Muuto, is only one day away! This year's exhibition showcases the works of 17 emerging designers and artists from across the world with the ambition to facilitate and nurture the future of new perspectives on design.
—
September 16th — 26th, 2021
Ukurant Perspectives 2021, supported by Muuto
Amaliegade 38
1256 Copenhagen K

#muuto #newperspectives #scandinaviandesign

node.text:
For Ukurant Perspectives 2021, supported by Muuto, design duo Davide Ronco and Pablo Dorigo have created pieces that explore the concept of negative space in the Muuto universe. The pieces can be experienced at both the Ukurant Perspectives 2021 exhibition and the Muuto HQ during 3daysofdesign, starting tomorrow, September 16th.
—
September 16th — 18th, 2021
Muuto HQ
Østergade 36-38
1100 Copenhagen K

September 16th — 26th, 2021
Ukurant Perspectives 2021, supported by Muuto
Amaliegade 38
1256 Copenhagen K

#muuto #newperspectives #scandinaviandesign

node.text:
3daysofdesign is only two days away and we invite you to discover our collection of new perspectives alongside informal meetings with designers Anderssen & Voll and Thomas Bentzen during this year's 3daysofdesign.

We will also be showing a special preview of this year's Ukurant exhibition, supported by Muuto, through unique design pieces.

Read more about this year’s 3daysofdesign and learn when designers Anderssen & Voll and Thomas Bentzen will be in our showroom, now via link in bio.

16—18 September
Muuto HQ
Østergade 36-38
DK-1100 Copenhagen K

node.text:
News: Introducing Raise Carafe & Glasses by Broberg & Ridderstråle—a subtle, mouth-blown and characterful glassware inspired by modernist still life paintings yet interpreted in contemporary shapes and colors.
—
Explore our new designs, now via link in bio.

Our new designs will be available in stores throughout this fall.
Please note that the design will be available in North America in early 2022.

#muuto #newperspectives #scandinaviandesign

Photo by @petrabindel
